Lucien Deslinires (1857, Vierzon -1937, Vernouillet) was a French journalist, writer and socialist. Deslinires joined the Parti Ouvrier Franais (POF) in 1891. He later tried unsuccessfully to establish a collectivist settlement in Mexico. After the Russian Revolution, he travelled to the USSR, becoming an agricultural commissar in the Ukraine in 1920. Civil war and shortage of money blocking his schemes of agrarian reform, he returned to France.[1] 
